AIGER is a format, library and set of utilities for And-Inverter Graphs (AIGs).

The focus is on conversion utilities and a generic reader and writer API. 
There is no real general purpose AIG library included, though the 'smvtoaig'
utility uses AIGs as intermediate representation.

  documentation:

    README                       this file
    FORMAT                       detailed description of the format
    LICENSE                      BSD style license

  library:

    aiger.h                      API for the AIGER library ('aiger.c')
    aiger.c                      read and write AIGs in AIGER format

  examples:

    examples/*.aig               simple examples discussed in 'FORMAT'
    examples/*.aag               (same in ASCII format)

    examples/read.c              decoder code for binary integer repr.
    examples/write.c             encoder code for binary integer repr.

    examples/poormanaigtocnf.c   simple application reading BIG format
                                 without use of the AIGER library
                                 (prototype for competition readers)
  utilities:

    aignm     show symbol table of AIG
    aigsim    simulate AIG
    aigstrip  strip simbols from AIG file
    aigtoaig  translates AIG formats (ascii, binary)
    aigtocnf  translate combinational AIG into a CNF
    aigtosmv  translate sequential AIG to SMV format
    smvtoaig  translate flat boolean encoded SMV model to AIG

    andtoaig  translate file of ANDs into AIG (currently broken)

Armin Biere, Johannes Kepler University, October 2006.
